{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περι-κλάω</b>, <br /> <b>twist round, bend</b>, [τὴν φλόγα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Igne” 53; τοὺς ἀγκῶνας LXX.4Mac.10.6 \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]: but usually <b>break off</b>, [τὰς δρῦς] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 9.18 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; τῷ κράνει π. τὸ ξίφος <b>break</b> it <b>round</b> the helmet, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Sulla” 14 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, περικεκλασμέναι ῥάβδοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 4.6.10; περικλασθήσονται κλῶνες LXX.Wis.4.5; κολοσσὸς -κλασθεὶς ἀπὸ τῶν γονάτων 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 14.25 \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]; περικλώμενα τοῖς αὑτῶν βρίθεσι <b>bent and broken</b> by.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Sulla” 12 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; περικεκλασμένον σχῆμα <b>bent and bowed down</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.878c \">Refs</a>]; of persons, τοῖς σώμασι -κλώμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Physiognomonica” 813a16, compare 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 21.48 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; but also, <b>arched</b>, θώραξ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 18(1).420; περικλώμενος κλύδων 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Antiquitates Judaicae” 15.9.6. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Optics, <b>refract</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Cleomedes Astronomus 2.1 (_passive_). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>wheel</b> an army <b>round</b> to the right or left, ἐπὶ δόρυ or ἐπ᾽ ἀσπίδα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 11.12.4, compare 11.23.2 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; also π. τὸν Τίβεριν ἐπὶ τὸ Κίρκαιον <b>divert</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Caesar” 58. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, of missiles, <b>ricochet</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-2nd c.BC: Philo Mechanicus “(Belopoeica) Excerpte aus Philons Mechanik - Ath. Berl. Akad.” 79.19. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> τόποι περικεκλασμένοι <b>rough, broken</b> ground, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 12.20.6 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; so λόφοι περικεκλ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 18.22.9 \">Refs</a>]; οἰκίαι περικεκλ. houses <b>on such ground</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.26A. 7; περικεκλασμένας λόφοις ἐρημίας 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 6.7. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G20942","accentedUnicode":"περικλάω","shortDef":"on such ground","mediumDef":"on such ground","stepGloss":"to break","stepTransliteration":"periklaō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}